reviewText:
Early Access Review

A Rock n Roll Concert Themed Tower Defensehttps://youtu.be/i8iIO4n3m2U
+ The soundtrack / background music is great especially if you are into rock
+ Interesting comical theme where you are trying to defend against pop and hipsters I believe.
+ Visually the levels look quite nice, and I enjoyed watching the little band play on stage

This game is in EARLY ACCESS, so don't take these negatives too seriously
- The towers (speakers) sound effects are AWFUL, and really get in the way of listening to the music
-  Balancing issues, in my experience only 1 of the towers is of any use, and the rest don't seem to do as much or anything differently while being more expensive (= useless)
- Sometimes the towers miss" their targets which is extremely frusterating considering there's not much you can do to avoid this...
- I felt like you are given too little coins in the beginning and it almost forces you to rely on the early wave start bonus to stay alive
date: but then later on it seems to get too easy (especially considering you don't need to build the other types of towers)   (this is another balancing issue)\n\n~ I'd like to see more variety between each level
votesTotal: I think it's an amusing but pretty basic tower defense that is mainly focused toward people who like Rock 'N' Roll music. The game in it's current state is not "amazing"
votesFunny: but considering this just came out in Early Access I can see it getting a lot better later on.\n\n"
